non_compliant.amend: This text does not appear to be a privacy policy and does not contain information about data collection or processing.  To comply with GDPR, a privacy policy must be provided when collecting personal data from a data subject.  This policy should clearly and concisely explain what information is being collected, the purpose of processing, how long it will be stored, and the data subject's rights.  If data is collected from other sources, this must also be disclosed to the data subject.
